  "bookId": 72,
  "firstAcquaintance": "With the New Year arrived, Metori dons a kimono and transforms into a refined, gentle young lady. Is this the mysterious power of the New Year? No, it's the power of red envelope money.",
  "personality": "During the New Year, she starts using polite language and lowers her voice. However, her polite words always come with hints to 'be generous.' She may seem well-mannered, but she's actually transformed into a little devil who goes straight for your wallet.",
  "like": "Grilled meat, red envelopes",
  "familiarData": "Metori isn't really that fond of money, but money can buy what she wants. So she learned from Jiulian and decided to be a good kid during the New Year to collect red envelope money. Of course, the main reason is that it's just really fun. And so, the festival-limited Nadeshiko Metori was born.\n\nThough she's only a well-behaved child for a limited time, the docile Metori is genuinely endearing and successfully collected quite a bit of red envelope money. She did cut into Jiulian's territory a bit, though. Hopefully the two can maintain their good relationship.\n\nHer outfit was once again sent by a mysterious tailor. It fits surprisingly well and looks absolutely adorable. That white scarf in particular makes Metori look quite elegant.\n\n'Come to think of it, I don't remember this scarf being in the clothes that were sent over?'\n'Master, being too nitpicky during the New Year makes you a cheapskate, you know.'",
